article.description: — Luka Sakota's 17 points helped Northeastern defeat Boston University 67-58 on Monday night in a season opener.
article.headline: Sakota puts up 17, Northeastern takes down Boston University 67-58
article.linkText: Sakota puts up 17, Northeastern takes down Boston University 67-58
article.story: BOSTON -- — Luka Sakota's 17 points helped Northeastern defeat Boston University 67-58 on Monday night in a season opener. Sakota also contributed five assists for the Huskies. Chris Doherty scored 15 points and added 10 rebounds. Joe Pridgen had 10 points and was 4-of-13 shooting (1 for 4 from 3-point range). Kyrone Alexander finished with 15 points for the Terriers. Matai Baptiste added 11 points for Boston University. In addition, Ethan Okwuosa finished with nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
